# NestJS Patterns

## Layer responsibilities

| Layer | Responsibility | Forbidden |
|-------|---------------|-----------|
| Controller | HTTP in/out, route params, status codes | Business logic, DB access |
| Service | Business logic, DB access via Prisma | HTTP concerns, req/res objects |
| Module | Wire controllers + providers | Business logic |
| DTO | Input shape + validation decorators | Logic, DB calls |

## Controllers — HTTP boundary only

```ts
// ✅ correct — delegate everything
@Post('run')
@HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)
run(@Body() dto: RunScenarioDto) {
  return this.scenariosService.run(dto);
}

// ❌ wrong — DB in controller
@Post('run')
async run(@Body() dto: RunScenarioDto) {
  const run = await this.prisma.scenarioRun.create({ data: dto }); // forbidden
  return run;
}
```

## Services — own all logic

```ts
// ✅ correct
@Injectable()
export class ScenariosService {
  private readonly logger = new Logger(ScenariosService.name);
  constructor(private readonly prisma: PrismaService) {}

  async run(dto: RunScenarioDto) {
    const run = await this.prisma.scenarioRun.create({
      data: { type: dto.type, status: 'pending' },
    });
    return { id: run.id, status: run.status, createdAt: run.createdAt };
  }
}

// ❌ wrong — instantiate dependencies manually
export class ScenariosService {
  private prisma = new PrismaClient();  // never
}
```

## DTOs — validate every input

```ts
// ✅ correct
export class RunScenarioDto {
  @IsString()
  @IsNotEmpty()
  @MaxLength(100)
  type: string;

  @IsOptional()
  @IsObject()
  metadata?: Record<string, unknown>;
}

// ❌ wrong — untyped body
@Post() run(@Body() body: any) { ... }
```

## Modules — one per feature

```ts
// ✅ correct
@Module({
  controllers: [ScenariosController],
  providers: [ScenariosService],
})
export class ScenariosModule {}

// ❌ wrong — everything in AppModule
@Module({
  providers: [ScenariosService, HealthService, MetricsService],
})
export class AppModule {}
```

## Global infrastructure modules

`PrismaModule` and `MetricsModule` are `@Global()` — import them only in `AppModule`.
Never import them in feature modules.

## Exception types — use NestJS built-ins

See `error-handling.mdc` for the full exception map.
Never throw raw `Error` from a service or controller.
